    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1953-09-04T03:30:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1953-09-04T03:30:00-05:00" n="364"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d364">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">888.00 TA/9–453: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 364<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Iran (<persName corresp="#p_HLW1"
                            type="from">Henderson</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Department of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d364fn1">Also sent to <gloss target="#t_FOA1">FOA</gloss>
                        and repeated to London.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tehran</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1953-09-04T12:00:00+03:30"
                            >September 4, 1953—noon</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>584. Re <gloss target="#t_Tecto1">Tecto</gloss> 217 September 2, 1953
                    antepenultimate paragraph.<note n="2" xml:id="d364fn2">Reference is to the
                        following question asked by <gloss target="#t_FOA1">FOA</gloss>: Would
                            <persName corresp="#p_ZMF1">Zahedi</persName> be agreeable to signing a
                        formal commitment regarding East-West trade in compliance with the Battle
                        Act? (888.00 TA/9–353)</note>
                </p>
                <pb facs="0816" n="790" xml:id="pg_790"/>
                <p>At conclusion our conversation last night with <persName corresp="#p_ZMF1"
                        >Zahedi</persName> (<gloss target="#t_Embtel1">Embtel</gloss> 582 September
                    3 London 178)<note n="3" xml:id="d364fn3">Not printed. (888.00 TA/9–353)</note>
                    I referred in presence <persName corresp="#p_WWE1">Warne</persName> and
                        <persName corresp="#p_NPH1">Paul</persName> to informal statement made by
                    him to us on August 31, (<gloss target="#t_Embtel1">Embtel</gloss> 539,
                    September 1 paragraph 2) to effect Iran would not sell strategic materials or
                    commodities to Soviet Union. I said it might be extremely embarrassing to US if
                    after we had begun extending aid to Iran on substantial scale Iran Government
                    would begin sell strategic materials to Iron Curtain countries. It would be
                    helpful therefore if Prime Minister could assure us again at this time that Iran
                    would not sell to Soviet Union materials and commodities which US considered to
                    be of strategic character. Embassy has prepared supply Prime Minister list these
                    strategic materials prepared in accordance with US law commonly referred to as
                    “Battle Act”. Prime Minister said he had no hesitation in giving us assurances
                    not only that would Iran not sell materials of strategic character to Iron
                    Curtain countries but that it would probably not sell some of the materials set
                    forth in list of commodities mentioned in SovietIranian treaty signed earlier in
                    day.</p>
                <p>2. I hope this statement by <persName corresp="#p_ZMF1">Zahedi</persName> will
                    satisfy Department and <gloss target="#t_FOA1">FOA</gloss> re Iranian intentions
                    not to sell strategic materials to Iron Curtain countries. We are privately
                    providing Prime Minister with Battle Act list (<gloss target="#t_Deptel1"
                        >Deptel</gloss> 673 September 1).<note n="4" xml:id="d364fn4">Not printed.
                        (460.889/9–153) On Sept. 11 the Department informed the Embassy that
                            <persName corresp="#p_ZMF1">Zahedi</persName>’s statement was
                        satisfactory for Battle Act purposes. (Telegram 750; 888.00 TA/9–353)</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_HLW1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Henderson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
